an operating model that describes the stock and fleet dynamics in the historical period, and the assumptions for the projection period;
an observation model that is used to generate the simulated fishery data in the projection period;
a set of alternative management procedures (interchangeably referred to as harvest strategies, or management strategies) that use the simulated fishery data to generate a management recommendation (e.g., a total allowable catch (TAC) or effort control). In some cases this can be a stock assessment model that estimates the status of the (simulated) stock and linked to a harvest control rule to generate management advice from the output of the assessment. In other cases, the management procedure can be simple empirical rules that produce management advice directly from the observed fishery data (e.g., an index targeting method). The key feature of a management procedure is that it is reproducible and objective: that is, the same data will always result in the same management recommendation;
an implementation model that describes how the management advice generated by the management procedures is implemented back into the simulated fishery.

Welcome
Welcome to the openMSE Technical Manual developed and written by Adrian Hordyk, Quang Huynh, and Tom Carruthers from Blue Matter Science.
This book is intended for fisheries scientists and other analysts who wish to learn how to use openMSE for all aspects of Management Strategy Evaluation (MSE):

building operating models;
developing management procedures;
conducting closed-loop simulation testing;
summarizing and presenting results.

For more general information about openMSE see the openMSE website.

This Technical Manual has been developed for openMSE 2.0, which is currently under development and will be released in 2025. The code in this manual is only compatible with the development branches of MSEtool, SAMtool, DLMtool, and openMSE. Unless you are feeling particulary adventurous, you should not use the development code for your analyses!
